<subSubSection id="60504858D809275AF97C48BCA3A68811" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="2ECD4E3991FD56C9F1A566B657D99A0E" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="884E6C2894E820FC2D60764D72B4EAC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A Balkan Peninsula endemic known to occur in the northern parts of Greece, with Mt. Pangeo, Mt. Orvilos, Mt. Menikio and Mt. Falakro shaping its distribution to the NE (
<bibRefCitation id="4FD8DEA242AD252F54383F71B47AB291" author="Akeroyd, J. R." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667680" refString="Akeroyd, J. R., 1986. Mountain Flora of Greece 1. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 1" year="1986">Akeroyd 1986</bibRefCitation>
). The new population on Mt. Achladovouno is the easternmost known record in the Greek territory.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
